
1. What is correlation in simple words?

Correlation shows the relationship strength between two variables—how much one changes when the other changes. High correlation means predictable movement together; low correlation means independent movement.​

Analogy: Ice cream sales and sunglasses purchases both rise in summer (positive correlation), but neither causes the other.



2. What is positive and negative correlation?

| Type         | Pattern                         | Example                           |
| ------------ | ------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Positive (+) | Both increase/decrease together | Height ↑ → Weight ↑               |
| Negative (-) | One increases, other decreases  | Speed ↑ → Braking distance ↑ jmp​ |
| None (0)     | No predictable pattern          | Shoe size vs IQ                   |

