3. What is the range of correlation?

Correlation coefficient (r) ranges from -1 to +1:

| Value | Strength         | Meaning            |
| ----- | ---------------- | ------------------ |
| +1.0  | Perfect positive | Exact linear rise  |
| +0.7  | Strong positive  | Clear relationship |
| +0.3  | Weak positive    | Slight tendency    |
| 0.0   | No correlation   | Independent        |
| -0.3  | Weak negative    | Slight opposite    |
| -1.0  | Perfect negative | Exact linear fall  |



4. Does correlation mean causation?

Correlation shows association only, NOT cause-effect:​

text
❌ Wrong: "Ice cream sales cause drownings" (both rise in summer)
✅ Right: "Summer heat drives both ice cream sales AND swimming"

Classic trap: Firefighters and fire damage correlate (both high at big fires)

Proof needed: Controlled experiments, not just correlation.



5. Where is correlation used in real life?

